<TITLE> Tight security at ZIA ahead of Jalil's flight </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 3 (bdnews24.com)  Security was tightened in and around Zia International Airport ahead of Awami League general secretary Abdul Jalil's flight to Singapore late Monday night, a police officer said. The AL leader"critically" ill with heart and kidney ailmentswas released on one-month parole for medical treatment abroad. Khandaker Rafiqul Islam, deputy police commissioner for Uttara Zone, told bdnews24.com that more than 150 police personnel had been deployed at the airport. The Rapid Action Battalion and other security agencies mounted watch in the area to avert what the police officer said was any untoward incident. The police also tightened security around the house of Jalil's Gulshan home where he had gone from LabAid Cardiac Hospital to spend some time with his family, before his flight scheduled for an 11:55pm takeoff. bdnews
